{"TopicId":214391,"ForumId":198,"TopicTitle":"Suggest auto info headers when starting bug report.","CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T14:21:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-04T14:21:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuggest that when you start a bug report (or a support request) it comes with the required information headers itemised in the \u0022Stock Support \u0026amp; Bug Reporting Guide\u0022 preincluded as editable text headers. As this will save everyone time and effort, will encourage good practice and an atmosphere of mutual support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EKSP Version\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EOperating System and version \u00A0(Windows 10, Windows 11)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ECPU and GPU models, any other system\u00A0information which could be relevant\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription of the bug. \u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpected Behavior\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObserved Behavior\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESteps to Replicate\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFixes / Workarounds (if known..)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA list of ALL mods. \u00A0If the list is long, please consider using a spoiler window.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOther Notes / Screenshots / Log Files (if possible..)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI got the idea from the Empyrion boards where new bug threads have exactly that kind of support which is helpful, see for yourself at\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://empyriononline.com/forums/bugs.24/create-thread\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://empyriononline.com/forums/bugs.24/create-thread\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-04T14:22:15Z\u0022 title=\u002203/04/2023 02:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 4, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by boolybooly\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}